                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-08T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 8, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>97. Department’s telegram No. 46, August 8, 10 a.m. and my telegram No. 95,
                    August 8, 1 [<hi rend="italic">5?</hi>] p.m. Exchange of notes now completed
                    both bearing date August 6th. Executive decree is expected to be signed shortly:
                    will advise.</p>
                <p>Because Ministries have ceased administrative functions it is believed further
                    changes could not be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
